50|$|Within the <b>European</b> <b>Patent</b> Office, {{examiners}} are {{in charge}} of studying <b>European</b> <b>patent</b> <b>applications,</b> filed by applicants, in order to decide whether to grant a patent for an invention. The patents granted by the <b>European</b> <b>Patent</b> Office are called <b>European</b> <b>patents.</b>|$|R
